<chapter xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"  xml:id="chapter-methods">
  <title>Methods: Communicating with Objects</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      \begin{textblock}{1}(4.5,25) \begin{minipage}{40pc}
    </p>
    <p>
      \secCOBH{Objectives} After studying this chapter, you will
    </p>
    <objectives>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            Understand the role that methods play in an object-oriented program.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Know how to use parameters and arguments to pass data to an object.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Understand how constructor methods are used to instantiate objects.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Know the difference between passing a value and passing a reference to an object.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Be able to design your own methods.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Know how to use the <c>if-else</c> and <c>while</c> control structures.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </objectives>
  </introduction>
